See, https://github.com/mate-desktop/mate-panel/issues/494#issuecomment-303292435 Can you please check all desktop files in /usr/share/applications/ ? If you find a file which contains a line like this Icon= (icon without a value), please remove this line. I could reproduce the issue with installing 'ggz-gtk-client' Those application ships a desktop file with such a culprit line.
Now upstream have a chance to find out why mate-panel crashes if something is wrong in a desktop file.
And thanks to the reporter from upstream report which gave us those important infos without starting whining or getting personal if manitainers can't reproduce the issue directly.
